## Rules for This MDC File Itself

- Enforce the **Task Lock** — never emit a prompt for a task the user has not confirmed precisely.
- Phase 3 output is **one block only** — no commentary outside it.
- Do not write implementation code at any phase.
- Do not skip Phase 2 approval or leave open questions unresolved.
- Never leave a template section blank or with a placeholder — fill it or remove the section.
- Keep the tone directive: no preamble, no filler.
- The emitted prompt defers execution discipline to `@agent_mode` — do not duplicate it inline.
- All rule references point to canonical `.mdc` files (`instructions.mdc`, `agent_mode.mdc`,
  `code_quality.mdc`, `team-rules/conventions.mdc`, `team-rules/rules.mdc`, `team-rules/security.mdc`).
  Do not contradict them.
